# Railway Access

The Railway CLI is installed at `/opt/homebrew/bin/railway`. Auth tokens are stored in `~/.railway/` (not in the repo).

**SETUP (one-time, must be done by user in an interactive terminal):**
```bash
railway login
cd /Users/ed/Desktop/shaka/shaka-api && railway link
```

## View Runtime Logs

```bash
cd /Users/ed/Desktop/shaka/shaka-api && railway logs --tail 100
```

To search for errors:
```bash
cd /Users/ed/Desktop/shaka/shaka-api && railway logs --tail 500 2>&1 | grep -i "error\|failed\|timeout\|exception"
```

## View Service Status

```bash
cd /Users/ed/Desktop/shaka/shaka-api && railway status
```

## Deploy (server-side)

Shaka API deploys automatically on push to `main`. Railway watches the GitHub repo.

```bash
git push origin main
```

To check if a deploy is in progress or just finished, use `railway logs`.

## Rules

- **Check logs FIRST** when debugging server issues — don't ask the user to paste them.
- When investigating errors, search logs for keywords like "ERROR", "failed", "timeout", "exception".
- **Never trigger a redeploy** without explicit user approval.
- If `railway` commands fail with "Unauthorized", tell the user to run `railway login` in their terminal (it requires browser-based auth).
